        "category": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> Reading or touching the scroll.</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> A weeks-long vision in seconds: being caught betraying the castle; both ankles broken by Kazavon; weeks subsisting on worms in a cave; the crawl back to a corpse-field of slaughtered orcs and humans; a gleaming sword; the dawning horror that the betrayed party was <strong>Zon-Kuthon himself</strong> — transformation, and flight into the deep with the prize. Then @Check[type:will|dc:23] or be cursed (9th-rank): the victim <em>knows</em> himself a worm, no longer believes he can or should walk, drops @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone}, and must crawl wherever he travels until the curse is counteracted — or Kleestad dies.</p>"
        },
